Civil society, too, showed signs of resilience. The grassroots group Indivisible ran \'93One Million Rising\'94 training sessions to prepare people for organizing and protest. On July 17, more than 1,500 demonstrations took place across the country under the banner \'93Good Trouble Lives On,\'94 honoring John Lewis and calling for voting rights and justice. In Baltimore, a suite of local programs\'97the Safe Streets violence interrupters, the Group Violence Reduction Strategy, a Summer Youth Engagement Strategy, and a school-based intervention pilot\'97continued to show measurable reductions in shootings and youth victimization, offering a different model of public safety rooted in community rather than coercion.\
